==English==
===Proper Noun===
'''Negro''' plural negros, negroes (Often capitalized) 
#''Archaic.'' A person of [[sub-Saharan]] [[African]] descent; [[black]].
====Derived terms====
*[[negress]]
*[[negroid]]

====Translation====
* Dutch: [[neger]] ''m'', [[negerin]] ''f''
* Finnish: [[neekeri]]
* German: [[Neger]] ''m'', [[Negerin]] ''f''
* Portuguese: negro ''m'', [[negra]] ''f''
* Slovak: [[černoch]] ''m'', [[černoška]] ''f''
* Spanish: negro ''m'', [[negra]] ''f''

===Adjective===
'''negro'''

#''Archaic.'' Relating to the black ethnicity 
#''Archaic.'' Black or dark brown in color.

==== Translations ====
* Dutch: [[zwart]], [[zwarte]]
* Slovak: [[černošský]] -á -é (1), [[čierny]] -a -e (1, 2)

=== Usage Note ===
#The word is considered acceptable only in a historical context. [[Black]] and if applicable (though to a lesser extent) [[African-American]] are the prefered alternatives.

